<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-07-24T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-07-24T16:00:00-05:00" n="544" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d544">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2870: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-24T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 24,
                                            1920—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>780. Your 1075, July 16, 5 p.m.</p>
                            <p>Japanese Ambassador [<hi rend="italic">Chargé</hi>] communicated to
                                the Department of State October 8, 1919,<note n="66" xml:id="d544fn66"><ref target="frus1919v01#pg_492"><hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1919, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 492</ref>.</note> Japanese
                                Government’s acceptance of the formula submitted by the French
                                Government in the sense of the modified form as suggested by the
                                American Government referred to in your Despatch 1061 of July 21,
                                    1919.<note n="67" xml:id="d544fn67"><ref target="frus1919v01#pg_468"><hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p.
                                        468</ref>.</note></p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>